geolosys.guide.chapter.stones.name=Stone Variants
geolosys.guide.chapter.stones.text=Vanilla stone variants can be (if enabled) clustered into large plutons, instead of generating sporadically throughout the world.
geolosys.guide.chapter.coal.name=Coal
geolosys.guide.chapter.coal.text=Coal is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0, and can drop sulfur if another mod adds it. Coal ore can also drop Peat, Lignite, Bitumen or Anthracite (in addition to normal coal); what it drops depends on your §ldepth§r§0. The previous list is in order from highest to lowest in depth, and lowest to highest in flamability (in a furnace).
geolosys.guide.chapter.cinnabar.name=Cinnabar
geolosys.guide.chapter.cinnabar.text=Cinnabar is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0, and can drop Redstone Crystals from Extra Utils 2 or Cinnabar from Thermal Expansion (random change based on Fortune). §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.gold.name=Gold
geolosys.guide.chapter.gold.text=Gold from Geolosys behaves similarly to Vanilla, and is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.lapis.name=Lapis
geolosys.guide.chapter.lapis.text=Lapis from Geolosys behaves similarly to Vanilla, and is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a stone pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.quartz.name=Assorted Quartz
geolosys.guide.chapter.quartz.text=Assorted Quartz drops a variety of different Quartzes if available. Such varieties include Actually Additions' Black Quartz and Applied Energistics' Charged and Uncharged Certus Quartz. Assorted Quartz is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a stone pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.kimberlite.name=Kimberlite
geolosys.guide.chapter.kimberlite.text=Kimberlite from Geolosys is the realistic alternative to Vanilla's diamond ore. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.beryl.name=Beryl
geolosys.guide.chapter.beryl.text=Beryl from Geolosys is the realistic alternative to Vanilla's emerald ore. It can generate in any biome, and is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0

geolosys.guide.chapter.hematite.name=Hematite
geolosys.guide.chapter.hematite.text=Hematite is (intended, at least) smaller, easier to access resource for Iron. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a stone pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.limonite.name=Limonite
geolosys.guide.chapter.limonite.text=Limonite is a larger, harder to access resource for both Iron and Nickel. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.malachite.name=Malachite
geolosys.guide.chapter.malachite.text=Malachite is (intended, at least) smaller, easier to access resource for Copper. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a stone pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.azurite.name=Azurite
geolosys.guide.chapter.azurite.text=Azurite is a larger, harder to access resource for Copper. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.cassiterite.name=Cassiterite
geolosys.guide.chapter.cassiterite.text=Cassiterite is (intended, at least) smaller, easier to access resource for Tin. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a stone pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.teallite.name=Teallite
geolosys.guide.chapter.teallite.text=Teallite is a larger, harder to access resource for Tin. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.galena.name=Galena
geolosys.guide.chapter.galena.text=Galena is a large resource for Silver and Lead. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.bauxite.name=Bauxite
geolosys.guide.chapter.bauxite.text=Bauxite is a large resource for Aluminum / Bauxite (depending on the mod). It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires a wooden pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.platinum.name=Platinum
geolosys.guide.chapter.platinum.text=Platinum is the primary resource for Platinum, and can drop Osmium if enabled. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.autunite.name=Autunite
geolosys.guide.chapter.autunite.text=Autunite is the primary resource for Uranium, and can drop Yellorium if enabled. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0
geolosys.guide.chapter.sphalerite.name=Sphalerite
geolosys.guide.chapter.sphalerite.text=Sphalerite is the primary resource for Zinc. It is found between §3<maxY> and <minY>§0. §4Requires an iron pickaxe.§0

